The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 May is 274,606 (31,649.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 May, there were 1,058 new confirmed cases (121.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 April, there were 1,721 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 39% (663 fewer cases).
